							<p>The block-chain data structure is a back-linked list of blocks of transactions, which is ordered. Each block is identifiable by a hash, generated using the sha256 cryographic hash algorithm on the header of the block. Blockchains help prevent single points of failure by having each new block be generated in relation to the hash of the previous block. This creates a chain of linked blocks. Block-chain helps secure connections between clients while saving time and money.</p>
