							</header>
							<p>We made a decentralized passport verification system to prevent people from altering passports or creating fake passports. The benefits of this system include speeding up the passport verification process (leading to shorter wait times at airports, for example) as well as increasing the ease of verification. We will do this by using blockchain.</p>
							<p>Everyone's passport will contain a digital part. This patr will store passport info, and this info can be used by a verification system to verify the passport. This will include a record of when the passport is used as well as several identical databases.  Each database will hold everyone's passport data, stored in blocks. When someone tries using their passport, the blockchain of passport data will be chcked among all of the databases in the verification system. If valid, the system will then add the record to the passport, and update all the databases. The passport cannot be altered because as soon as it is, the has changes and no longer matches any of the verification databases. The result is a secure system to hold passport data. The system could flourish into more practical uses concerning security through E-Mails and Cyber Security.</p>
						
